      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STORMY SEAS (5) is a first starter by The Autumn Sun for the Messara/Gavranich stable. Showed little in four trials then ran a close third at Muswellbrook on 22 April. Half-brother to a stakes winner. Finds a soft race to launch his career. ARTIE'S MAGIC (2) went close two runs back over a similar trip to this at Muswellbrook then had plenty go wrong at Taree last time in a run worth forgetting. Nicely drawn and well in after the claim so conditions are right for a return to form. VENDOR (6) returns after a 160-day spell. Likely to be better for this hit-out but in a race that lacks depth he has the ability to play a leading role. PENINHAND (7) made further improvement last start at the third run of the campaign, battling on well for third over 1280m at Muswellbrook. Draws the fence and will be at her peak. NEAREST (3) failed as a $1.50 favourite on debut last start at Tamworth. Worth another chance with the blinkers going on today.",
